items.question: I feel like I’m actively outgrowing older versions of myself.
I feel like I’m living out someone else’s expectations, not my own.
I feel scattered — like I’m playing different roles in different contexts without a center.
I feel confident in my rhythm — my way of being fits this moment.
I feel like I’m hiding my real strategy because it wouldn’t be accepted here.
I feel pressure to keep solving things using the same mindset, even when it's not working.
I often feel energized, clear, and aligned with what I'm doing.
I’ve locked myself into a pattern that’s no longer working, but I can’t break out of it.
I feel like I’ve shut something essential down inside myself to keep going.
